column5: Got out AGAIN yesterday for some more fall walleye action...  The numbers were low but the size was a bit better...  We got 14 walleye and anothe nice bonus musky...  Biggest walleye were 5lb 7.2lb and 8.3lb  We did everything yesterday... Jig... Troll... Rig/minnow... And all techniques caught fish...
Mike again outstanding - I cannot wait to share a couple of days with you next year - good clean outstanding action! I am getting cabin fever after putting boat away last weekend.
ENOUGH....I CAN'T take it anymore....my boat is in storage and it's suppose to be hunting season.

Stop nothing MIKE , keep it coming . i for one allways like hearing the news from back home .... lol . Nice chop on i see behind you , plus another great catch ..... Where is the line for the Mohawk waters ?
Nice work buddy !!! Dang, your brother looks like your Dad !! A few less wrinkles,mind you Keep livin the dream Guys !!!!
As long as your catching them Mike, keep the pics coming man...
Seems like you get a bonus musky nearly everytime you go for walleye. Ever land a monster walleye while fishing for musky?
Musky and walleye together.... sounds like my kinda day!!  Nice fish man.
I had a call today saying Bob Isumi was doing walleye in the same spot yesterday , any signs of him Mike ?
Those are some nce patterns on those fish!
Really nice clean fish dude.  Enjoy the weather while you can, it's looking above seasonal for the next little while.  I know I will.
Sweet! Mike where are you fishing? May want to book with you next year..I added you as a friend on FB.. will be in touch. Id love some of those big eyes... Musky would be an awesome bonus too!
Clean looking fish, the bonus musky was a nice surprise I'm sure.
Nice Cabelas Guidewear!  Oh yeah, nice fishies too!
